<TITLE> BNP standing committee meets at new Gulshan office </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)BNP's highest policy making body held a meeting at the new Gulshan office of its chairperson on Tuesday. Party joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan told bdnews24.com BNP chief Khaleda Zia had called the standing committee meeting to address party policy issues. This is the second meeting of the standing committee since Khaleda's release from special jail on Sept 11. The earlier meeting was held at the party's Naya Paltan central office on Sept 13. Party secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain, standing committee members M Saifur Rahman, Abdul Matin Chowdhury, Dr RA Gani, Tanveer Ahmed Siddiqui, M Shamsul Islam and retired Lt Gen Mahbubur Rahman attended Tuesday's meeting. Of the 11 standing committee members Barrister Moudud Ahmed and Dr Khondker Mosharraf Hossain are now in jail. Another member Khandker Mahbubuddin Ahmed did not attend the meeting as his brother, Dhaka University law faculty's former dean Prof KAA Kamruddin, died recently. Before the meeting began, leaders of Bangladesh Hindu Boudha Christian Kalyan Front led by BNP joint secretary general Goyeshwar Chandra Roy met with Khaleda to convey Durga Puja greetings. bdnews
